When you expect primitive `byte[]`, the result type should be `_byte[]`.  
This is because `byte` is an alias of `java.lang.Byte` (see the [doc](https://mybatis.org/mybatis-3/configuration.html#typealiases)).  

```xml
&lt;select id=&quot;getPhoto&quot; resultType=&quot;_byte[]&quot;&gt;
...
```

Also, when there is a Java mapper interface and the return type of the mapper method is `byte[]`, MyBatis expects multiple rows with a column of `byte`.  
So, the return type of the method must be `Object` in that case.  
You should be able to cast the returned object to `byte[]`.

Optionally, it is possible to define a default method in the interface that performs the cast.

```java
interface YourMapper {
  Object _getPhoto(String param);

  default byte[] getPhoto(String param) {
    return (byte[])_getPhoto(param);
  }
}
```

